The paper deals with the problem of routing in graphs, which is a fundamental topic in computer science. The use of node-disjoint paths and constant congestion suggests that the paper is related to network routing and graph theory, which are covered by cs.NI and cs.DS. The fact that the paper deals with directed graphs and minor-free graphs suggests that it may also be related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may also be related to theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
